@carrielewis

Sorry to disagree with SP, but gold stars are given only for current puzzles.  There is apparently some leeway (I don’t know the specific limits because I always solve the night they come out), but some have said that as long as you don’t solve the new one, you can solve the previous one for the gold.  It is not clear how long that lasts, but some say that after several days, that’s not true anymore. 

Solving from the Archive I’ll only get you blue stars.

@Dan

90 degrees is where a person going in a straight line stops going north and starts going south, or vice versa.

(For clues like that one, you have to give some latitude.)

@Helen Wright
Anymore, I play sporadically, and I always use the same opening word. I can see on the old lists that it has already come up as a solution, on one of the days I didn't play. So, I missed my chance for a hole-in-one; but I use it anyway.
(My WPA is about 3.7)

@Nick
And to rephrase what I commented yesterday: don't kids have to memorize capitals any more? I learned in 9th grade that Bolivia had two.
  Is it the only one?

@RozzieGrandma

Unfortunately, and also sometimes fortunately, there are many things I have forgotten from the 9th grade...  and before and since. 😆  

I only knew of Sucre as the capital, myself, and that's only because I play a geography game to help me with such things. I have to look that one up after I finished the puzzle because I was so surprised it wasn't so Sucre.  It was interesting to learn that there are two capitals.
